---
import CodeBlock from './primitives/CodeBlock.astro';
---

<section id="install" class="relative py-24 md:py-32 mesh-stage">
  <div class="mesh-bg-faint" aria-hidden="true"></div>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-page px-6">
    <header class="max-w-prose">
      <p class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-fg-3 mb-4">§05 · Install</p>
      <h2 class="text-h2 font-medium text-fg-0 text-balance">Sixty seconds to a running dashboard.</h2>
      <p class="mt-5 text-lead text-fg-1 text-pretty max-w-[60ch]">
        Two paths. Pick the one that matches the box you have lying around.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="mt-14 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 lg:gap-10">
      <!-- Local — Docker Compose -->
      <div class="install-block relative group">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2.5">
            <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" class="install-icon text-argus-green/85" aria-hidden="true"><rect x="2" y="7" width="20" height="14" rx="2"/><path d="M2 11h20"/></svg>
            <h3 class="install-title text-fg-0 text-[18px] font-medium">Local · Docker Compose</h3>
          </div>
          <span class="font-mono text-[10.5px] text-fg-3">recommended for trying it out</span>
        </div>

        <CodeBlock
          lang="bash"
          code={`git clone https://github.com/kr4t0n/argus
cd argus
cp .env.example .env
docker compose up -d`}
        />

        <p class="mt-4 text-[13.5px] text-fg-2 max-w-[52ch] text-pretty">
          Brings up Postgres, Redis, the server, and the web app on
          <span class="code-chip">localhost:3000</span>. The bundled stack ships a sidecar on the host so you can
          spin a Claude Code or Codex agent immediately.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Cluster — Helm -->
      <div class="install-block relative group">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2.5">
            <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" class="install-icon text-argus-green/85" aria-hidden="true"><polygon points="12 2 22 8.5 22 15.5 12 22 2 15.5 2 8.5 12 2"/><line x1="12" y1="22" x2="12" y2="15.5"/><polyline points="22 8.5 12 15.5 2 8.5"/></svg>
            <h3 class="install-title text-fg-0 text-[18px] font-medium">Cluster · Helm</h3>
          </div>
          <span class="font-mono text-[10.5px] text-fg-3">production deploys</span>
        </div>

        <CodeBlock
          lang="bash"
          code={`helm repo add argus https://kr4t0n.github.io/argus/helm
helm repo update
helm install argus argus/argus \\
  --set postgres.url=$POSTGRES_URL \\
  --set redis.url=$REDIS_URL`}
        />

        <p class="mt-4 text-[13.5px] text-fg-2 max-w-[52ch] text-pretty">
          BYO Postgres and Redis, or run them in-cluster. Full chart docs in
          <a href="https://github.com/kr4t0n/argus/blob/main/helm/argus/README.md" rel="noopener">helm/argus/README.md</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Sidecars on remote boxes -->
    <div class="mt-16">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-6 md:gap-16 items-start">
        <div>
          <p class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-fg-3 mb-3">Adding remote machines</p>
          <h3 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg-0 max-w-[16ch] text-balance">One sidecar per box. systemd or launchd.</h3>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="text-fg-1 max-w-[60ch] text-pretty">
            Each remote box runs a single <span class="code-chip">argus-sidecar</span> binary. Hand it a server URL and a join token,
            wrap it in a unit file, and it self-registers as a Machine on first dial-home.
            Recipes for systemd, launchd, and a one-line shell installer in the
            <a href="https://github.com/kr4t0n/argus/blob/main/INSTALLATION.md" rel="noopener">install guide</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  /* Hover the whole install block: title goes brand green, icon stroke
     brightens, the closing prose lifts from dim to full. CodeBlock
     handles its own bg lift. No green halo. */
  .install-block .install-prose,
  .install-block > p:last-of-type {
    transition: opacity var(--t-hover), color var(--t-hover);
    opacity: 0.7;
  }
  .install-block .install-title,
  .install-block .install-icon {
    transition: color var(--t-hover);
  }
  .install-block:hover .install-prose,
  .install-block:hover > p:last-of-type {
    opacity: 1;
  }
  .install-block:hover .install-title {
    color: oklch(0.78 0.17 158);
  }
  .install-block:hover .install-icon {
    color: oklch(0.78 0.17 158);
  }
</style>
